com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.hystrix

Class CachingCommand<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.netflix.hystrix.HystrixCommand<T>
      • com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.hystrix.Command<T>
        • com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.hystrix.CachingCommand<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the function represented by this command.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.netflix.hystrix.HystrixExecutable<T>, com.netflix.hystrix.HystrixInvokable<T>, com.netflix.hystrix.HystrixInvokableInfo<T>, com.netflix.hystrix.HystrixObservable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CachingErpCommand

    public abstract class CachingCommand<T>
extends Command<T>
    Abstract class implementing a Hystrix protected command with the possibility to cache the result.

    The implementing class needs to implement the runCacheable() and the getCache() methods. The key of the cache is, by default in getCommandCacheKey(), based on the current tenant and user, as well as the class name of the executed command.

      • useCache

        protected boolean useCache()
        Returns:
        true if the cache is actually used, false otherwise.

      • getCache

        @Nonnull
protected abstract com.google.common.cache.Cache<CacheKey,T> getCache()
        Returns the instance of the command-specific cache. Note that each command should have its own static cache.

        Example usage: 

         
 private static final Cache<CacheKey, T> cache = CacheManager.register(CacheBuilder.build(MyClass.class));
 
  @Override
 protected final Cache<CacheKey, T> getCache()
 {
     return cache;
 }
        Returns:
        The command-specific cache.

      • getCacheKey

        @Deprecated
 @Nullable
protected final String getCacheKey()
        Deprecated. Use getCommandCacheKey() instead.
        Returns:
        Always null since the internal Hystrix caching mechanism is obsolete when using a CachingCommand which introduces a cache across requests.

      • getCommandCacheKey

        @Nullable
protected CacheKey getCommandCacheKey()
                                         throws TenantAccessException,
                                                UserAccessException
        Returns the CacheKey that is used by this command. By default, this is a CacheKey.ofTenantAndUserIsolation() appended with the full class name of this command.
        Returns:
        The CacheKey for this command. If null is returned, the cache is not used.
        Throws:
        TenantAccessException - If there is an issue while accessing the tenant.
        UserAccessException - If there is an issue while accessing the user.
